entities.context: Primary meal kit subscription service with self-managing accounts

entities.name: Factor
entities.context: Ready-to-eat meal service being cross-sold to HelloFresh customers, causing confusion and complaints

insights: Significant customer confusion about Factor cross-sell program - customers unaware they ordered Factor meals or how the two services interact
Multiple complaints about unauthorized or unexpected Factor orders being placed on HelloFresh accounts
Customers unclear that canceling HelloFresh affects Factor ordering ability, and vice versa
Communication gap: customers not understanding Factor meals come in separate boxes and require separate ordering
Account management issues: customers struggling with meal plan changes, cancellations, and understanding the relationship between HelloFresh and Factor subscriptions
At least one customer filed a dispute and vowed never to order again due to confusion
Technical glitches reported (website pricing discrepancies, orders placed despite items removed from cart)
Cross-sell program appears to be causing customer dissatisfaction and account cancellations
